    title: 'Home charging vs public charging: what does an EV really cost per mile?',
    description: 'Calculate EV charging cost per mile from home, public AC and DC fast-charging rates, charging losses, kWh share, subscriptions and session fees.',
    faq: [
      { question: 'How do I calculate EV charging cost per mile?', answer: 'Multiply miles by kWh per 100 miles, add charging loss, then multiply grid kWh by a rate weighted across home, public AC and DC charging. Add memberships and session or idle fees, then divide the annual total by annual miles.' },
      { question: 'Should I use the EV dashboard consumption or electricity from the wall?', answer: 'Dashboard consumption usually represents energy used by the vehicle, while the bill or charger records energy delivered. If you start with dashboard kWh per 100 miles, add charging loss; if you already measured wall-to-wheel consumption, do not add it again.' },
